title: UD’s Tucker notches 300th win
text:
Posted: 10:45 a.m. Monday, Oct. 19, 2015 UD’s Tucker notches 300th win Related University of Dayton soccer coach Mike Tucker won his 300th career game Sunday when the Flyers knocked off Fordham. FILE PHOTO Sponsored Links By Staff Staff Writer 
University of Dayton women’s soccer coach Mike Tucker notched career win No. 300 on Sunday as the Flyers defeated Fordham 3-1 at Baujan Field. 
Tucker, in his 21st season at Dayton, is 300-114-29 overall and 159-31-10 in the Atlantic 10. 
Tucker is one of just 17 active coaches to have won 300 matches in NCAA Division I women’s soccer. 
Ashley Campbell scored two goals and had an assist in the win. Campbell has 57 career goals, and is just one away from equaling UD’s all-time leading goal scorer mark.
